109784.name: Number of children who are stunted (OWID based on UNICEF/WHO)
109784.description:
The number of children younger than five who are stunted – significantly shorter than the average for their age, as a consequence of poor nutrition and/or repeated infection.

Stunting in children is defined as being less than two standard deviations below the median height for their age.
109784.datasetName: Number of children who are stunted (OWID based on UNICEF/WHO)

source.name: OWID based on UNICEF/WHO
source.dataPublisherSource: UNICEF, WHO, World Bank: Joint child malnutrition estimates (JME). Aggregation is based on UNICEF, WHO, and the World Bank harmonized dataset (adjusted, comparable data) and methodology.
source.additionalInfo: This dataset multiplies the stunting prevalence figures from UNICEF/WHO by the under 5 population (UN Population Division 2017)
